  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Report suspicious transactions\n2. Maintain transaction records\n3. Implement customer identification programs\n4. Screen for potential money laundering activities\n\nInternational organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) also set global standards for combating money laundering. Penalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.",
